args: I've heard great things about a well-known\nseer somewhere 'round here...
No need to look too hard, Ranzal.\nHonestly, I'm not really into fortune-\ntelling to begin with.
Don't be a downer! I'm gonna find me...\nOoooh! I think we struck gold.
Wait, THAT'S what you heard great\nthings about?!
Bwa ha ha! Nah, that was just an aside.\nDon't worry—her skills are top-notch.
...Uh-oh. Looks like she's already got a\ncustomer.
...So how compatible do you think the two\nof us are? Lately, it feels like he's always\nbeing cold to me.
Secret?! I knew it! He's cheating on me!
No. It is you I see reflected, not him.\nAre you not the one who has a secret?
I but reveal the destiny I see reflected\nin the orbuculum's surface.
But...but I can't possibly tell him the truth!
Do not fear. The future I see for you is\na most positive one.
I am certain that he will accept the truth\nif you share it with him.
Y-you really think so?\n...All right. I'll try telling him.
Thank you very much! I'm feeling a little\nmore courageous now.
I am happy to have been of use.\nMay your future be prosperous.
Bwa ha! Fortune-telling's amazin', yeah?\nWho knew you could know someone's\nsecrets usin' some crystal ball?
Ah. I didn't know I had another visitor.\nIt is exceedingly impolite to listen\nin on other people's divinations.
Sorry, sorry. Just couldn't help ourselves.\nRight, {player_name}?
Your skills are impressive—I think I might\nbe scared to have my fortune told after\nseeing that.
Heh heh. You have nothing to fear.\nCome along now.
C'mon, {player_name}.\nGet her to tell ya yer future.
That's what I brought ya here for!\nYer fortune is all of our fortunes, yeah?
Then look into the crystal ball's surface...\nGently regulate your breathing...
Let your heart be at peace...\nLet your mind... No!
The heck?! She just fell to the floor!
A violent clash... Light and darkness met\none another head-on, only to repel and\nscatter in all directions.
That's the vision I saw in you.\nIt was...exceedingly powerful.
I know not if it bodes good or ill.\nI've never seen anything like it.
I wouldn't have dragged ya here if I knew\nwe were gonna get some kinda foreboding\nresult like that.

Besides, we don't even know for sure if it's
a good omen or a bad one—which means
we'll just try our best to make everything
end well.
Then please allow me to help you.
Seers share with others what destiny has\nin store for them, then help guide them\nalong the proper path.
But we are also warriors who fight against\nthe bounds of fate itself.
After seeing a destiny as terrible as yours,\nI cannot just stand by and leave you to\nfight it alone.
Uhhh, so whatcha wanna do here,\n{player_name}?
The more allies we have, the better.\nWhat's your name?
My name is Verica. It's a pleasure to make\nyour acquaintance.
I'm {player_name}, and we're\ndelighted to have you.
Gotta say, this ain't really what I was\nexpectin' when I brought ya here.
Maybe not, but it's always nice to have\nmore help. So I'm glad I came.
I'm no expert on fortune-telling, but I'd say\nthat alone is a good omen for the future.
Man, you really can find a bright side in\nwhatever life throws at ya!
A strong spirit such as yours will be\nessential in standing up to fate.
(But that vision I saw was less a clash\nbetween light and dark, and more...)
(More a vision of light being gradually\nswallowed up by a vast darkness.)
(What terrible fate lies in store for this\npoor young man?)
(Well, no matter the end, it is now my\ncharge to watch over him as it happens.)
